## Entry 2: During Their First Use of Product (The Skeptical Leap)

*10:15 PM, Thursday*

Okay. I did it. I finally pulled the trigger. 

I’ve been researching this AI trading tool for the last three days. I’ve read the whitepapers, I’ve scrutinized the backtesting data, and I’ve run the numbers through my own spreadsheets until my vision blurred. It claims an 18% monthly return. My cynical, engineer brain immediately screamed "scam." But the logic… the logic actually holds up. It’s an algorithmic hybrid, stripping out the emotional human error that wrecked me last year. 

I linked my account tonight. It’s $100 a month for accounts under $25k. I spend more than that on coffee and my climbing gym membership. It’s a calculated risk. An experiment.

My stomach is still in knots, though. It feels weird handing over the keys to a machine. I sat there watching the dashboard initialize, the little green status indicators lighting up. It felt like I was launching a rocket, but I’m not the one steering. 

I’m terrified it’s going to glitch and wipe out my initial deposit. But I’m also… buzzing. There’s this electric current of hope running through me that I haven’t felt in years. What if this is the edge I’ve been looking for? What if this is the "hack" that finally breaks me out of this agonizingly slow crawl toward wealth? 

I’m going to check it tomorrow morning. I probably won’t sleep much tonight. I just need to see it make one logical, profitable trade. Just one. Prove to me the math works in the real world, not just on paper.

