## Entry 3: After Using The Product (The Awakening)

*8:30 AM, Saturday*

I am sitting on my balcony with a cup of coffee, and for the first time in as long as I can remember, my chest doesn’t feel tight. The low-grade hum of anxiety that usually soundtracks my mornings is just… gone. 

It’s been two months. I just checked my dashboard. 

The AI hit the 18% target. Again. 

I literally laughed out loud when I saw the number. It was this sharp, disbelieving bark of laughter. While I was sleeping, while I was stuck in a brutal three-hour code review, while I was at the climbing gym… this silent, beautiful piece of software was working. It was analyzing the market, executing trades with zero hesitation, zero fear, zero human error. 

It made more money this week than I did at my actual job. 

I feel like I’ve been unplugged from the Matrix. I’ve spent my entire adult life trading my time for money, believing the lie that the only way to build wealth was to suffer through the corporate grind for four decades. I was so angry, so exhausted. 

Now? I feel powerful. I feel like I finally have leverage. 

I was doing the math this morning—real math, not the depressing calculations I used to do. If this compounding continues, my FIRE (Financial Independence, Retire Early) date just moved up by a decade. A full decade of my life, handed back to me. 

I don’t have to be chained to that desk forever. I don’t have to settle for the slow lane. I finally found the edge. I’m going to up my deposit next month. The machine is awake, and for the first time, so am I.
